With income inequality at a 100-year high, passing the American Stability Act is more urgent than ever. 

This bill is about restoring fairness to an economy that has left working families behind for far too long.

The bill also cuts taxes for working families by eliminating federal income tax on wages needed for basic living expenses, while adding a surtax on incomes over $1 million and $15 million, so billionaires finally pay their fair share.

The American Stability Act raises the minimum wage to $15 an hour immediately, with a 10% annual increase until it hits $20 an hour. This ensures wages finally reflect the real cost of living for workers across the country.

Today, we introduced the American Stability Act—the largest wage increase and tax cut for working families in U.S. history. 

It’s time we end a system that rigs the economy against working people and gives tax breaks to billionaires. https://t.co/u6YevyoJfJ
